☕ Java Has-A Relationship (Composition/Aggregation) Practice Questions (Basic → Advanced)
🟢 Basic Level (1–5)
1. Create a Car class that has an Engine object. Display the engine details.
2. Create a Student class that has an Address object. Print the student's name and address.
3. Create a Person class that has a Passport object. Display both person's and passport details.
4. Create a Book class that has an Author object. Print the book title and author name.
5. Create a Mobile class that has a Battery object. Display battery capacity and mobile brand.
🟡 Intermediate Level (6–10)
6. Create an Employee class that has a Department object. Display employee and department information.
7. Create a School class that has a Principal object. Print school and principal details.
8. Create a Laptop class that has a Processor object. Display processor details along with laptop information.
9. Create a Hospital class that has a Doctor object. Print hospital name and doctor details.
10. Create a BankAccount class that has a Customer object. Display customer and account details.
🔴 Advanced Level (11–15)
11. Create a University class that has many Student objects.
12. Create a Library class that has many Book objects and display all books.
13. Create a Company class that has many Employee objects and print all employee details.
14. Create a Team class that has many Player objects and display the team information.
15. Create an Order class that has many Product objects and calculate the total bill.
🏆 Interview Challenge (16–20)
16. Create a College class that has many Department objects.
17. Create a House class that has many Room objects and display all room details.
18. Create a Computer class that has CPU, RAM, and HardDisk objects.
19. Create a Restaurant class that has many MenuItem objects and print the menu.
20. Create an ECommerce system where a Customer has many Order objects, and each Order has many Product objects.